values:
i just got off the phone with this guy for a job as "creative professional" i really like the title - i have no clue what it entails, but i like the title. it turns out its a tiny marketing company who directs clients to jobs in the healthcare profession or something like that. whatever i have an interview on wednesday. i doubt its the sorta thing i'd like to do, but right now my options are so limited. that;s what happens when you hate working with people, food, retail etc.&nbsp;

cmj is such a tease, i love it, oh how i love it. free tickets, cds, really cool bands just popping in to play an acoustic gig here or there (like brakesbrakesbrakes and they played porucine or pineapple!). and then i get to blog about&nbsp;it.&nbsp;my supervisor is awesome, her bosses are even awesome too. sigh. i need money.&nbsp;i will cry when it is august. for multiple reasons.

also my laptop died a few days ago (i'm using my sis's now). no surprise really. grah. i&nbsp;went to the mac store. one the guys there was pretty cute and tried to sell me a comp. he said he went to college for three years and then dropped out to 'pursue the music thing'. hawt. i am thinking of going there wednesday to actually buy a comp (grad present from the parents).
